
[1]advised

   ADVI'SED, pp.

   1. Informed; counseled; also cautious; prudent; acting with
   deliberation.

   Let him be advised in his answers.

   With the well advised is wisdom. Prov. 13.

   2. Done, formed, or taken with advice or deliberation; intended; as, an
   advised act or scheme.
